Les Miserables;;83;;75;;PG-13;;After serving a lengthy prison sentence, Jean Valjean (Liam Neeson) turns his life around after an act of kindness opens his eyes, becoming a beloved mayor of a French town. A policeman, Javert (Geoffrey Rush), who was a prison guard when Valjean was locked up, has a vendetta against him and tries to denounce him as a criminal despite a lack of evidence. Spanning several decades, the story of Javert and Valjean's rivalry is set against the backdrop of post-Revolution French society.;;History,Drama;;Bille August;;1998;;Liam Neeson,Geoffrey Rush,Uma Thurman,Claire Danes,Hans Matheson,Reine Brynolfsson,Peter Vaughan,Mimi Newman;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/1083326-les_miserables